cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language generation using a neural sequence generation model. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses the training of the model and the use of embeddings. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with the development of an AI-based method for generating clinical text. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper uses a neural network architecture for the model. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with generating text based on medical concepts and relations, which could be seen as a form of information retrieval.
